FBIS3-32315 "drlat025_a_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 February 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Lage Meets Brizola in Rio Before Departing for Colombia FL0702022394 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in Spanish 0100 GMT 7 Feb 94 FL0702022394 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] In the final stage of his six-day official visit to Brazil, Cuban Vice President Carlos Lage today met with Rio de Janeiro Governor Leonel Brizola and had lunch with Roberto Marinho, president of the GLOBO NEWS AGENCY. He also met with leaders of the Workers Party and Brazilian businessmen from the tobacco and energy areas. Previously Lage had met with President Itamar Franco. Tomorrow the Cuban delegation will leave for Bogota, Colombia.
